message.content: The president of the United States in 1996 was William Jefferson Clinton. He served as the 42nd president of the United States from January 20, 1993, to January 20, 2001. During his time in office, he implemented several policies and programs aimed at improving the economy, education, healthcare, and social welfare in the country. He was also involved in several foreign policy initiatives, including the signing of the North American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA) and the implementation of economic sanctions against Iraq. Clinton was impeached by the House of Representatives in 1998 on charges of perjury and obstruction of justice, but he was acquitted by the Senate and remained in office until the end of his term.
